div.p:
Judged by the outline of the entrance, a cave in the shape of square box with open front
                            in standard size is originally planned (fig.

                            ).

Section H, direction 135˚; ca. 1.7 m to the north-east of Cave 98, floor about 0.14 m higher than that of Cave 98;
                            ca. 1.27 m to the south-west of Cave 100, floor about 0.65 m
                            lower than that of Cave 100 (fig. ).

Section H, direction 122˚; ca. 2 m to the north-east of Cave 104, at the same level with Cave 104;
                            ca. 45.8 m to the south-west of Cave 104-2, separated by a
                            steep rocky slope (fig. ).

Section H, direction 122˚; ca. 45.8 m to the north-east of Cave 104-1, separated by a steep rocky slope, without direct access (fig.
                                ); at the same level with Cave 104-3 ca. 0.7 m to the north-east, with which a double-cave
                            is formed.

Section H, in the area called
                            Dingjiayan; direction 145˚; ca. 1.65 m
                            north-east of Cave 107; ca. 0.68 m south-west of sutra Cave 109;
                             ca.
                            3.20–5 m above the foot of the cliff, and ca. 13 m above the water level (fig.
                                ).

Square box with open front; double reveal visible on wall f (fig.

                               ); striations fairly systematical (fig.
                                   ), but not polished.

Section H, direction 145˚; ca. 42.8 m north-east of Cave 114;
                            ca. 22 m south-west of Cave 115-1 (fig. ). The floor is about 5 m lower than that of
                            Cave 115-1. Being secluded, it is difficult to access (fig. ).
